# Animation_Design

## 1. Applies when
Games with character animation, creature animation, facial animation, or cutscene animation.

## 2. This document owns
Animation style, principles, and quality targets.
Character locomotion, combat, and interaction animations.
Facial animation and lip-sync specifications.
Creature and enemy animation behaviors.
Animation state machine design (in coordination with Gameplay_Systems).
Cutscene animation direction and keyframe specifications.
Animation blending, layering, and IK systems.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Rigging and skeleton setup (→ Technical_Art).
Animation Blueprint implementation (→ Technical_Design).
Cutscene scripting and timing (→ Narrative_Pipeline).
Gameplay state transitions that trigger animations (→ Gameplay_Systems).

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Animation Style & Principles · 2. Character Locomotion ·
3. Combat & Interaction Animations · 4. Facial Animation & Lip-Sync ·
5. Creature & Enemy Animation · 6. Animation State Machines ·
7. Cutscene Animation · 8. Blending, Layering & IK

## 5. Common boundaries
- Animation owns "how it moves"; Gameplay_Systems owns "when it triggers".
- State machine transitions belong in both docs (coordination boundary).
- Facial animation references Narrative_Script for dialogue beats.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Check cross-references with Gameplay_Systems for trigger conditions.
- Check cross-references with Character_Sheets for character-specific animation notes.
